<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Scheme  
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Scheme">
	A Scheme is an Activity method that provides the identification and description of an intended course of action to accomplish an objective. 
	A Scheme enables the ordering of entries. 
	Dates and times may be specified for entries and time intervals between entries.

	<note>A Scheme may be classified as a Plan or Schedule, and it may be further classified into specific types of Plans or Schedules.</note>

<example>Acquisition plan, Maintenance plan, Resource schedule are examples of schemes. </example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Scheme_entry  
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry">
	A Scheme_entry is an Activity method that provides the identification and description of a single entry in a specific 
	<express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme"/>.

	<note number="1">A Scheme_entry may be associated with time constraints.</note>

	<note number="2">A Scheme_entry only exists within the scope of a specific 
	<express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme"/>.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Scheme_entry  Attribute: scheme 
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry.scheme"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry.scheme">
	the <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme"/> into which the scheme_entry is included.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Scheme_entry_assignment  
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry_assignment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry_assignment">
	A Scheme_entry_item_assignment is an Applied_activity_method_assignment that associates a Scheme_entry with one of more items.

	<note>The Scheme_entry_assignment links the single items included in Plans and Schedules with their associated 
		<express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry"/>. 
		These items may be actions, events, or tasks depending on the nature of the Plan or Schedule.
	</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Scheme_entry_assignment  Attribute: assigned_entry 
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry_assignment.assigned_entry"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry_assignment.assigned_entry">
	the <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry"/> being assigned.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Scheme_entry_assignment  Attribute: items 
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry_assignment.items"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry_assignment.items">
	the items which are associated with a <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Scheme_entry_relationship  
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry_relationship"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry_relationship">
	A scheme_entry_relationship is an Activity_method_relationship relating two <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry"/> entities. 
	An association may exists between scheme_entry entities that relate to different schemes or between different 
	<express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry"/>
	entity instances for the same <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme"/>. 

	<note> The scheme_entry_relationship provides the ability to relate entries included in Plans or Schedules in different ways. By applying classifications on the scheme_entry_relationship it can be used for different purposes.</note>

<example>Decomposition, Dependency, and sequencing are examples of kinds of relationships possible between schema entries.</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Scheme_entry_relationship  Attribute: related_entry 
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry_relationship.related_entry"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry_relationship.related_entry">
	one of the <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry"/> entities which is a part of the relationship.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Scheme_entry_relationship  Attribute: relating_entry 
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry_relationship.relating_entry"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry_relationship.relating_entry">
the other <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry"/> which is a part of the relationship. If one element of the relationship is dependent upon the other then this attribute shall be the dependent one.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Scheme_relationship  
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_relationship"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Scheme_relationship">
	A <b>Scheme_relationship</b> is an <b>Activity_method_realtionship</b> relating two <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme"/>s.
 
<note>The Scheme_relationshipb
 provides the ability to relate Plans or Schedules represented by the 
	<express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme"/> 
	entity in different ways. By applying classifications on the <b>Scheme_relationship</b> it can be used for different purposes.</note>

<example>Decomposition, based-on, alternative, version are kinds  of relationships between <b>Scheme</b>s.</example> 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Scheme_relationship  Attribute: related_scheme 
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_relationship.related_scheme"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Scheme_relationship.related_scheme">
	one of the <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme"/>s which is a part of the relationship.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Scheme_relationship  Attribute: relating_scheme 
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_relationship.relating_scheme"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Scheme_relationship.relating_scheme">
	the other <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme"/> which is a part of the relationship.
	 If one element of the relationship is dependent upon the other then this attribute shall be the dependent one.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Scheme_subject_assignment  
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_subject_assignment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Scheme_subject_assignment">
	A <b>Scheme_subject_assignment</b> is the association of a 
	<express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme"/>
	with a specific subject.

	<note>The <b>Scheme_subject_assignment</b> links the Plans and Schedules with their associated subjects or targets. 
		This may indicate the intent of the scheme.
	</note>

	<example>
		The maintenance plan for an individual vehicle, 
		where the subject attribute points to the part_actual representing the individual vehicle.
	</example> 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Scheme_subject_assignment  Attribute: assigned_scheme 
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_subject_assignment.assigned_scheme"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Scheme_subject_assignment.assigned_scheme">
	the <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme"/>
	which is being associated to a subject.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Scheme_subject_assignment  Attribute: items 
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_subject_assignment.items"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Scheme_subject_assignment.items">
	the items to which a <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme"/> is associated.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Sequencing_relationship  
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Sequencing_relationship"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Sequencing_relationship">
	A sequencing_relationship is a 
	<express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry_relationship"/> 
	that defines a specific type of sequencing and relative timing for two <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Scheme_entry"/>. 
	<note number="1">Specific types of sequencing could include start-start, finish-start.</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Sequencing_relationship  Attribute: sequencing_type 
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Sequencing_relationship.sequencing_type"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Sequencing_relationship.sequencing_type">
	the type of sequencing between the relating_scheme_entry and related_scheme_entry.
	<example>finish_start, start_start, finish_finish, start_finish.</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Scheme_arm  Entity: Sequencing_relationship  Attribute: time_lag 
   <express_ref linkend="scheme:arm:Scheme_arm.Sequencing_relationship.time_lag"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Scheme_arm.Sequencing_relationship.time_lag">
	the amount of time, either positive or negative, before the sequencing applies between relating_scheme_entry and related_scheme_entry. 
	<note number="2">For a positive time_lag, the relating_scheme_entry is the later entry in time.</note>
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
